LogFile.FinalText: In many homes we find pets and many prefer to have either a dog or a cat. So far the soft young dog beats the dear kitten in the race for being Denmark's most popular pet. But while the dog's loyalty explains it large popularity, the numerous cat owners lov the cat's independence. While the general cat owner think that a dog is too independent and dirty, many dog owners see cats as lazy and inpersonal. Many pet owners choose a pet that reflects their own personality. When the big strong man buys himself a big strong dog, the dog's characteristics adds on to the ego of the dog owner. Conversely, the femine women often prefer the beautiful and elegant cat. Normally, the dog and the cat can get round without problems in agreement, if they are used to one another. Often, the dog owner and the cat owner quarrel more than the dog and the cat.
